Create a script file with ".sh" extension (FILE_NAME.sh). 
Make the script executable with command "chmod +x FILE_NAME.sh" for a script file. 
It is used for automation task, instead of doing manual human intervention.

Run the script in different ways. 
● . FILE_NAME.sh
● ./FILE_NAME
  ./FILE_NAME.sh
  ./FOLDER_NAME/FILE_NAME.sh
● sh FILE_NAME
  sh FILE_NAME.sh
● bash FILE_NAME.sh
● source FILE_NAME.sh
